<https://secure2.sla-online.co.uk//v3/Newsletter/NewsletterEmailExternalDisplay?newsletterEmailGuid=E91E4A24-D853-4015-9D19-FF3BB982251C>
Digital - Microsoft 365
Office 365 A1 Plus for education will retire on August 1 2024

Office 365 A1 Plus is being retired by Microsoft to ensure schools have
compliant licensing plans, and to support the transition to cloud licences
Microsoft 365 A3 and Microsoft 365 A5. Microsoft Office 365 A1 Plus program
is an Office subscription that includes Office desktop apps for qualified
schools that purchased Office institution-wide for faculty and staff.

Previously any school who purchased an Open Value Subscription Education
Solutions (OVS-ES) annual volume licence agreement would get the Office 365
A1 Plus licence added to their Microsoft 365 Tenancy. Find out more here.
<https://nyes.info/Newsletter/ExternalLink/208501?source=newsletter&guid=E91E4A24-D853-4015-9D19-FF3BB982251C>

If you have a Software and Infrastructure contract with NYES Digital, no
further action is required. The support team will check the licences for
you.

What happens if you don’t have the above contract?

Then…
If you’d like to check yourself, you can do this from the Microsoft 365
Admin Portal.

   1. Navigate to the M365 Admin Portal https://admin.microsoft.com
   <https://nyes.info/Newsletter/ExternalLink/208502?source=newsletter&guid=E91E4A24-D853-4015-9D19-FF3BB982251C>
-
   Login as your school's Microsoft 365 Administrator.
   2. On the left-hand navigation menu, go to Billing > Licenses.
   3. Look for Office 365 A1 Plus for Faculty and Office 365 A1 Plus for
   Student assigned licenses.

You will be currently using one of the following:

*Office 365 A1*
Free online Office productivity and learning tools. Includes online web
versions of Word, Excel, PowerPoint, OneNote, Microsoft Teams, and
additional classroom tools.
*Office 365 A1 Plus *
Offers everything that comes with Office 365 A1 and also includes the full
desktop apps for Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook) not
just the online web versions.

*After all existing Office 365 A1 Plus licences expire on August 1st, 2024,
schools will have the choice to:*

1. If the school has an active Microsoft OVS-ES volume licence agreement,
which includes the Desktop apps:

   1. Anyone with an A1 Plus licence after August 1st will need to be moved
   to an Office 365 A1 licence, the Office 365 A1 licences are free to schools.
   2. Request Microsoft 365 Apps for Enterprise licences added to the
   school Tenancy. This will add licences for the full Office Desktop apps.
   3. Assign M365 Apps for Enterprise to staff and students who require
   licences for the full desktop Office applications.

2. If the school does not have a valid OVS-ES agreement, the school can
purchase Microsoft 365 Education Cloud Solution Provided (CSP) A3 and A5
licences.


Do you have an Software and Infrastructure Service Level Agreement with
NYES Digital?

*Yes and have an active OVS-ES:*

   - NYES Digital will move all your Office 365 A1 Plus licensed users to
   Office 365 A1
   - NYES Digital will add the Microsoft 365 Apps for Enterprise to your
   Microsoft 365 Tenancy
   - NYES Digital will assign the Microsoft 365 Apps to the schools users
   who previously had A1 Plus licences.

*Yes but do not have an active OVS-ES agreement:*

   - NYES Digital will move all your Office A1 Plus licensed users to
   Office A1
   - NYES Digital will provide a quote for Microsoft 365 A3 licences for
   your Faculty and Students.

Customers with a Software and Infrastructure Service level Agreement with
NYES Digital will not need to do anything. NYES Digital will move your
licenses for you and if you have volume license OVS-ES agreement we will
ensure that your staff are provided with the Microsoft 365 Apps.

*No, you are not yet a customer of NYES Digital *
Please contact - nyes.digital@northyorks.gov.uk
<https://nyes.info/Newsletter/ExternalLink/211053?source=newsletter&guid=E91E4A24-D853-4015-9D19-FF3BB982251C>
and request a quote to manage your Microsoft 365 Tenancy, we will also be
able to provide you with Microsoft 365 A3 licences.

Should you have any questions or want to know more about the transition
process, please do not hesitate to contact our NYES Digital support team.

Email: nyes.digital@northyorks.gov.uk
Phone: 01609 536086

[required] Title: Re: Important Notification: CrowdStrike Update Issue Impacting Windows Systems
Description:
Hi,

A new updated has been shared by CrowdStrike:

Summary

  *   CrowdStrike is aware of reports of crashes on Windows hosts related to the Falcon Sensor.

Details

  *   Symptoms include hosts experiencing a bugcheck\blue screen error related to the Falcon Sensor.
  *   Windows hosts which have not been impacted do not require any action as the problematic channel file has been reverted.
  *   Windows hosts which are brought online after 0527 UTC will also not be impacted
  *   This issue is not impacting Mac- or Linux-based hosts
  *   Channel file "C-00000291*.sys" with timestamp of 0527 UTC or later is the reverted (good) version.
  *   Channel file "C-00000291*.sys" with timestamp of 0409 UTC is the problematic version.

Current Action

  *   CrowdStrike Engineering has identified a content deployment related to this issue and reverted those changes.
  *   If hosts are still crashing and unable to stay online to receive the Channel File Changes, the following steps can be used to workaround this issue:

Workaround Steps for individual hosts:

  *   Reboot the host to give it an opportunity to download the reverted channel file.  If the host crashes again, then:
     *   Boot Windows into Safe Mode or the Windows Recovery Environment
     *   Navigate to the %WINDIR%\System32\drivers\CrowdStrike directory
     *   Locate the file matching “C-00000291*.sys”, and delete it.
     *   Boot the host normally.

Note:  Bitlocker-encrypted hosts may require a recovery key.
Workaround Steps for public cloud or similar environment including virtual:
Option 1:

  *   Detach the operating system disk volume from the impacted virtual server
  *   Create a snapshot or backup of the disk volume before proceeding further as a precaution against unintended changes
  *   Attach/mount the volume to to a new virtual server
  *   Navigate to the %WINDIR%\\System32\drivers\CrowdStrike directory
  *   Locate the file matching “C-00000291*.sys”, and delete it.
  *   Detach the volume from the new virtual server
  *   Reattach the fixed volume to the impacted virtual server

Option 2:

  *   Roll back to a snapshot before 0409 UTC.

Workaround Steps for Azure via serial

  1.  Login to Azure console --> Go to Virtual Machines --> Select the VM
  2.  Upper left on console --> Click : "Connect" --> Click --> Connect --> Click "More ways to Connect"  --> Click : "Serial Console"
  3.  Step 3 : Once SAC has loaded, type in 'cmd' and press enter.
     *   type in 'cmd' command
     *   type in : ch -si 1
  4.  Press any key (space bar). Enter Administrator credentials
  5.  Type the following:
     *   bcdedit /set {current} safeboot minimal
     *   bcdedit /set {current} safeboot network
  6.  Restart VM
  7.  Optional: How to confirm the boot state? Run command:
     *   wmic COMPUTERSYSTEM GET BootupState

For additional information please see this Microsoft article<https://azure.status.microsoft/en-gb/status>.
Many thanks
--

[required] Title: Re: Important Notification: CrowdStrike Update Issue Impacting Windows Systems
Description:
Good Morning all,

As an addition to my previous email please find the below.

Workaround Steps for individual hosts:

  *   Reboot the host to give it an opportunity to download the reverted channel file.  If the host crashes again, then:
     *   Boot Windows into Safe Mode or the Windows Recovery Environment
     *   Navigate to the C:\Windows\System32\drivers\CrowdStrike directory
     *   Locate the file matching “C-00000291*.sys”, and delete it.
     *   Boot the host normally.

Note:  Bitlocker-encrypted hosts may require a recovery key.

Workaround Steps for public cloud or similar environment:

  *   Detach the operating system disk volume from the impacted virtual server
  *   Create a snapshot or backup of the disk volume before proceeding further as a precaution against unintended changes
  *   Attach/mount the volume to to a new virtual server
  *   Navigate to the C:\Windows\System32\drivers\CrowdStrike directory
  *   Locate the file matching “C-00000291*.sys”, and delete it.
  *   Detach the volume from the new virtual server
  *   Reattach the fixed volume to the impacted virtual server

 Please do not hesitate to reach out if you have any questions.
Many thanks
--

Subject: Important Notification: CrowdStrike Update Issue Impacting Windows Systems

Good Morning all,

Please find below CyberClans Statement regarding the CrowdStrike issue this morning 19/07.
We are writing to inform you that we are aware of a global issue with the latest update issued by CrowdStrike. This update is impacting certain Windows systems, causing them to become temporarily inoperable.
Please be assured that our team at CyberClan is actively monitoring the situation. We will work closely with you to implement a fix as soon as it is issued.
We apologise for any inconvenience this may cause and appreciate your patience and understanding. If you have any immediate concerns or require further assistance, please do not hesitate to contact our support team.
As an immediate fix please see below just issued by CrowdStrike
Summary
CrowdStrike is aware of reports of crashes on Windows hosts related to the Falcon Sensor.
Details
Symptoms include hosts experiencing a bugcheck\blue screen error related to the Falcon Sensor.
Current Action
CrowdStrike Engineering has identified a content deployment related to this issue and reverted those changes.
If hosts are still crashing and unable to stay online to receive the Channel File Changes, the following steps can be used to workaround this issue:
Workaround Steps:

  1.  Boot Windows into Safe Mode or the Windows Recovery Environment
  2.
Navigate to the “C:\Windows\System32\drivers\” directory
  3.  Locate the file matching “C-00000291*.sys”, and delete it.
  4.  Boot the host normally.

Please do not hesitate to reach out if you have any questions.
Many thanks

--

I am trying to update SIMS on our remote server, however Solus3 won't
install; the error I get through Solus is "access denied":
[image: image.png]

There are firewall rules in place which should (and have previously been)
sufficient.

Solus should automatically update SIMS; I have had issues with some devices
not doing this automatically however re-installing Solus usually gets round
it.

I did try disabling the firewall temporarily to see if that would fix it,
but that booted me out of the remote session and I have been unable to log
back in or reboot the server, so am now stuck.

If someone can help us to get the server back up and get Solus installed on
it that would be great. It may be the case that we need to enlist the help
of the SIMS helpdesk to get Solus to install, but I suspect it's a

James has kindly provided me with some instructions on how to access the School Calendar on Outlook, these are outlined below:



How to Add the 2023-2024 Huntington School Calendar



•         Step One: Open the Outlook desktop app (It will not work if using the web version of Outlook.)



•         Step Two: Click the three dots near the bottom left of Outlook, then select folders.





[cid:image001.jpg@01DAD83A.1F644A20]



•         Step Three: Scroll down the left-hand side panel until you see Public Folders, click the small ‘>’ arrow, the again click the next small ‘>’ beside All Public Folders.



•         Step Four: Once you have found the shared folder that says Huntington School Calendar 2023-2024, RIGHT click on it, then select add to favourites.





[cid:image002.jpg@01DAD83A.1F644A20]





•         Step Five: You now need to go to the calendar view at the bottom left of Outlook, click the small ‘>’ next to Other Calendars, then click the tick box for the Huntington School Calendar 2023-2024 and it should now appear in the main calendar view.



[cid:image003.jpg@01DAD83A.1F644A20]

James has kindly provided me with some instructions on how to access the School Calendar on Outlook, these are outlined below:



How to Add the 2023-2024 Huntington School Calendar



·         Step One: Open the Outlook desktop app (It will not work if using the web version of Outlook.)



·         Step Two: Click the three dots near the bottom left of Outlook, then select folders.





[cid:image007.jpg@01D9B327.F00B0210]



·         Step Three: Scroll down the left-hand side panel until you see Public Folders, click the small ‘>’ arrow, the again click the next small ‘>’ beside All Public Folders.



·         Step Four: Once you have found the shared folder that says Huntington School Calendar 2023-2024, RIGHT click on it, then select add to favourites.





[cid:image008.jpg@01D9B327.F00B0210]





·         Step Five: You now need to go to the calendar view at the bottom left of Outlook, click the small ‘>’ next to Other Calendars, then click the tick box for the Huntington School Calendar 2023-2024 and it should now appear in the main calendar view.



[cid:image009.jpg@01D9B327.F00B0210]

Digital - Microsoft 365
Office 365 A1 Plus for education will retire on August 1 2024

Office 365 A1 Plus is being retired by Microsoft to ensure schools have
compliant licensing plans, and to support the transition to cloud licences
Microsoft 365 A3 and Microsoft 365 A5. Microsoft Office 365 A1 Plus program
is an Office subscription that includes Office desktop apps for qualified
schools that purchased Office institution-wide for faculty and staff.

Previously any school who purchased an Open Value Subscription Education
Solutions (OVS-ES) annual volume licence agreement would get the Office 365
A1 Plus licence added to their Microsoft 365 Tenancy. Find out more here.
<https://nyes.info/Newsletter/ExternalLink/208501?source=newsletter&guid=293C9405-B48E-4EDF-96D7-81C7029245EF>

If you have a Software and Infrastructure contract with NYES Digital, no
further action is required. The support team will check the licences for
you.

What happens if you don’t have the above contract?

Then…
If you’d like to check yourself, you can do this from the Microsoft 365
Admin Portal.

   1. Navigate to the M365 Admin Portal https://admin.microsoft.com
   <https://nyes.info/Newsletter/ExternalLink/208502?source=newsletter&guid=293C9405-B48E-4EDF-96D7-81C7029245EF>
-
   Login as your school's Microsoft 365 Administrator.
   2. On the left-hand navigation menu, go to Billing > Licenses.
   3. Look for Office 365 A1 Plus for Faculty and Office 365 A1 Plus for
   Student assigned licenses.

You will be currently using one of the following:

*Office 365 A1*
Free online Office productivity and learning tools. Includes online web
versions of Word, Excel, PowerPoint, OneNote, Microsoft Teams, and
additional classroom tools.
*Office 365 A1 Plus *
Offers everything that comes with Office 365 A1 and also includes the full
desktop apps for Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook) not
just the online web versions.

*After all existing Office 365 A1 Plus licences expire on August 1st, 2024,
schools will have the choice to:*

1. If the school has an active Microsoft OVS-ES volume licence agreement,
which includes the Desktop apps:

   1. Anyone with an A1 Plus licence after August 1st will need to be moved
   to an Office 365 A1 licence, the Office 365 A1 licences are free to schools.
   2. Request Microsoft 365 Apps for Enterprise licences added to the
   school Tenancy. This will add licences for the full Office Desktop apps.
   3. Assign M365 Apps for Enterprise to staff and students who require
   licences for the full desktop Office applications.

2. If the school does not have a valid OVS-ES agreement, the school can
purchase Microsoft 365 Education Cloud Solution Provided (CSP) A3 and A5
licences.


Do you have an Software and Infrastructure Service Level Agreement with
NYES Digital?

*Yes and have an active OVS-ES:*

   - NYES Digital will move all your Office 365 A1 Plus licensed users to
   Office 365 A1
   - NYES Digital will add the Microsoft 365 Apps for Enterprise to your
   Microsoft 365 Tenancy
   - NYES Digital will assign the Microsoft 365 Apps to the schools users
   who previously had A1 Plus licences.

*Yes but do not have an active OVS-ES agreement:*

   - NYES Digital will move all your Office A1 Plus licensed users to
   Office A1
   - NYES Digital will provide a quote for Microsoft 365 A3 licences for
   your Faculty and Students.

Customers with a Software and Infrastructure Service level Agreement with
NYES Digital will not need to do anything. NYES Digital will move your
licenses for you and if you have volume license OVS-ES agreement we will
ensure that your staff are provided with the Microsoft 365 Apps.

*No, you are not yet a customer of NYES Digital *
Please contact - nyes.digital@northyorks.gov.uk
<https://nyes.info/Newsletter/ExternalLink/211053?source=newsletter&guid=293C9405-B48E-4EDF-96D7-81C7029245EF>
and request a quote to manage your Microsoft 365 Tenancy, we will also be
able to provide you with Microsoft 365 A3 licences.

Should you have any questions or want to know more about the transition
process, please do not hesitate to contact our NYES Digital support team.

Email: nyes.digital@northyorks.gov.uk
Phone: 01609 536086

Hi Craig, I wasn't sure who I needed to email about this but I have outlined the reasons why I need a laptop below.

The Animal Care Tech Award requires students to submit edited videos as part of their coursework. Over the last year I have been editing these at home, I have navigated my way through this process by getting out an old computer from my loft and setting it up in my bedroom. I have very little space and therefore it has been uncomfortable, I don't have a table in my bedroom, living room or kitchen and have been editing on the floor between my bed and the wall.

Each video takes on average 20 - 30 minutes to edit as they are 10 minutes long. I edit two videos per student over each moderation period, there are two moderation periods over the two years. This year I have two year 10 groups running alongside the yr 11s, resulting in the number of videos I will have to edit being greater than last year.

I have been using my own computer as I use CapCut to edit, this is not currently available in school. I also don't have enough time in the school day to do this at work therefore I had no choice other than to use my old computer last year so that the students could pass the course, due to a tight turnover

I would greatly appreciate a school laptop, with a big enough screen to edit on a timeline, and CapCut installed so that I can comfortably do this at home. The laptop would need enough hard drive space to store videos as I edit. I have tried out other editing software and found that I am more confident and fast with CapCut.

Please would you consider providing me with a laptop for these reasons so that I can work comfortably and efficiently. This will result in better time management for me and ensure videos are edited more effectively.

Let me know if you need anymore information.

Thank you!
Cherie

EXTERNAL - SRP1110 - Tang Hall Primary Academy | 04-DfE_School | Microsoft

guidance has also been issued by IT helpdesk in case you are having any
issues.  See below:





*Additional guidance for Teams external access provided by Unified
Communications Team is below : The guest user will be required to click on
the invitation link the DfE has sent to them; they will then be asked to
accept the terms and conditions and set up multi factor authentication. If
required they may wish to click 'set up another method' at the bottom and
choose the 'Phone' and then 'Text' option. Once they've got access, they
will be taken to a page that says 'My work apps'. They can ignore this, and
instead go back to their emails and look for an email which has the link to
the Team. They will then be required to click this and then accept the
terms of use. (If the user can't find this link, the owner of the team will
be required to send them the link to the Team.) If when clicking the link,
it says can't find this page, they will be required to open it in the web
app. Next steps will be to restart the Teams app, they should now click on
their profile photo in Teams in the top right, they will then see the
Department for Education account there where they can access the external
Teams' sites. If the user still can't access in the desktop app, ask them
to click on their profile photo in the web version to see if they can
access from here instead.*

Charlotte

I received an email from Lady Lumleys which was very unexpected.
I have investigated further and it is definitely a scam so I wanted to

clicked by someone who does have a child in this area who attends that
school.

*Kind Regards*

wasn't expecting so I just wanted to check if it was legit or actually a
phishing email from someone else.

recipients and contents and would rather check it out and also let you know

Brett Lightbody, Jun 28, 2024, 14:19 GMT+1

Hi Ben,

I believe the best way to resolve this would be for your IT to update the SSL certificate manually on the InVentry system with my below instructions.


1. _**On the sign in screen, triple click on the InVentry Logo on your home screen - this is usually in the bottom left of the screen**_
2. _**When the keypad appears enter the first 4 digits of your Anywhere ID (0632) or 1234**_
3. _**From the options that appear please select 'Shutdown InVentry', you will then see a normal PC desktop**_
4. _**An orange box will appear in the bottom right corner, please tap this then press 'Ok' in the window that appears in the centre of the screen (if you miss this the sign in screen will reload and you will need to complete the first 3 steps again.**_
5. _**Log off the InVentry_system user**_
6. _**Log onto the local admin user "Inventry" with the password "Inventry1983" (capital "i")**_
7. _**Run through steps 1-4 again to close down the software**_

Cut the "Silent Installer" folder to the below location.

C:\Program Files\Inventry\V4

Cut the 2 certificate files to the below location.

C:\Program Files\Inventry\V4\Service

Once the files are in the correct folders, go back into the "Silent Installer" and right click "Run as administrator" on the "Silent Installer.exe"

This should then present a CMD prompt and confirm the results of the SSL certificate update.

You can also confirm this by opening a new CMD window and entering the below command.

Netsh HTTP show sslcert

Please note you will have to extract the .RAR files.

Kind regards,
Brett.

Brett Lightbody, Jun 28, 2024, 14:19 GMT+1

Hi Ben,

I believe the best way to resolve this would be for your IT to update the SSL certificate manually on the InVentry system with my below instructions.


1. _**On the sign in screen, triple click on the InVentry Logo on your home screen - this is usually in the bottom left of the screen**_
2. _**When the keypad appears enter the first 4 digits of your Anywhere ID (0632) or 1234**_
3. _**From the options that appear please select 'Shutdown InVentry', you will then see a normal PC desktop**_
4. _**An orange box will appear in the bottom right corner, please tap this then press 'Ok' in the window that appears in the centre of the screen (if you miss this the sign in screen will reload and you will need to complete the first 3 steps again.**_
5. _**Log off the InVentry_system user**_
6. _**Log onto the local admin user "Inventry" with the password "Inventry1983" (capital "i")**_
7. _**Run through steps 1-4 again to close down the software**_

Cut the "Silent Installer" folder to the below location.

C:\Program Files\Inventry\V4

Cut the 2 certificate files to the below location.

C:\Program Files\Inventry\V4\Service

Once the files are in the correct folders, go back into the "Silent Installer" and right click "Run as administrator" on the "Silent Installer.exe"

This should then present a CMD prompt and confirm the results of the SSL certificate update.

You can also confirm this by opening a new CMD window and entering the below command.

Netsh HTTP show sslcert

Please note you will have to extract the .RAR files.

Kind regards,
Brett.

Hello

School need to follow the below to upload the preadmissions they do not
sync automatically.

*Pre-admission upload for schools using SIMS MIS*

If you use SIMS as your MIS then you can upload your pre-admission pupils
via MIS:Sync.
To do so:

   1. Log into MIS:Sync
   2. Select the *Preadmission* tab
   3. Select *Auto Update*

You will find your pre-admission students in *Group1 > Preadmissions* when
you search on your ParentPay site.

MIS:Sync will only update pre-admission pupils if they have a *Permanent
UPN number* or *Admission number *and in SIMS they are set to a status of
*Accepted*

*Please note: *Pre-admission pupil accounts will be converted to full pupil
accounts during your first upload of the new academic year and will retain
the same parent login details.

Any issues or questions please let me know.
